{
  "text": "The second MPL system employed [CITATION_1] , provides superior accuracy compared to the first one, but lower speed. It uses the same ultra-fast laser source and microscope objectives. For the fabrication of a polymeric scaffold, the laser beam remains immobile, while the sample moves using an xyz piezoelectric stages system, which allow fine and step movement (Physik Instrumente). This system was used to fabricate the structures of Fig. 3 . The average power employed for the structure fabrication was 5-15 mW, measured before the objective, while the average transmission was 20%. The scanning speed was set to 10-20 \u00b5m/s.",
